SB 1055/24 – EEE CF 5lr1420
By: Senator Kramer
Introduced and read first time: January 17, 2025
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Agriculture – Roosters – Restrictions
3 FOR the purpose of prohibiting, unless authorized by the Department of Agriculture, a
4 certain person from keeping a certain number of roosters on certain property
5 beginning on a certain date, subject to certain exceptions; authorizing the
6 Department to work in cooperation with a local animal control or law enforcement
7 officer to enforce this Act; and generally relating to restrictions on keeping roosters
8 in the State.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Agriculture
11 Section 3–105.2
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2016 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 Preamble
15 WHEREAS, Despite its illegality in Maryland, ongoing issues persist with
16 cockfighting; and
17 WHEREAS, Breeding roosters for cockfighting is directly linked to the spread of
18 Avian Flu; now, therefore,
19 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
20 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
21 Article – Agriculture
22 3–105.2.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
