2 SENATE BILL 375
1 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
2 INDICATED.
3 (2) “PROPERTY” MEANS:
4 (I) A PARCEL OF LAND; OR
5 (II) A COMBINATION OF PARCELS OF LAND OPERATING AS A
6 SINGLE UNIT.
7 (3) “ROOSTER” MEANS A MALE CHICKEN THAT:
8 (I) IS AT LEAST 6 MONTHS OLD;
9 (II) HAS FULLY DEVELOPED AN ADULT PLUMAGE; OR
10 (III) IS CAPABLE OF CROWING.
11 (B) THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO:
12 (1) COMMERCIAL POULTRY PRODUCERS, AS DEFINED IN § 8–704.2 OF
13 THIS ARTICLE;
14 (2) A PUBLIC SCHOOL OR NONPUBLIC SCHOOL THAT RECEIVES
15 STATE FUNDS;
16 (3) A GOVERNMENT–OPERATED ANIMAL SHELTER;
17 (4) AN ANIMAL WELFARE ORGANIZATION, AS DEFINED IN § 19–701 OF
18 THE BUSINESS REGULATION ARTICLE; OR
19 (5) A MEMBER OF A 4–H OR FUTURE FARMERS OF AMERICA
20 PROGRAM IF, ON REQUEST OF AN ANIMAL CONTROL OFFICER, AN OFFICER OF A
21 COUNTY HUMANE SOCIETY, OR A POLICE OFFICER, THE MEMBER PROVIDES IN
22 WRITING PROOF OF:
23 (I) MEMBERSHIP IN A 4–H OR FUTURE FARMERS OF AMERICA
24 PROGRAM; AND
25 (II) AUTHORIZATION FROM THE COUNTY IN WHICH THE
26 ROOSTERS ARE LOCATED THAT SPECIFIES:

SENATE BILL 375 3
1 1. THE REASON FOR KEEPING MORE THAN 5 ROOSTERS
2 PER ACRE OR MORE THAN 25 ROOSTERS ON A PROPERTY;
3 2. THE NUMBER OF ROOSTERS THAT MAY BE KEPT;
4 3. THE BREED OF EACH ROOSTER THAT MAY BE KEPT;
5 4. THE DURATION OF TIME EACH ROOSTER MAY BE
6 KEPT; AND
7 5. THE ADDRESS OF THE PROPERTY WHERE EACH
8 ROOSTER MAY BE KEPT.
9 (C) BEGINNING JANUARY 1, 2027, UNLESS AUTHORIZED BY THE
10 DEPARTMENT, A PERSON WHO KEEPS ROOSTERS THAT ARE MAINTAINED
11 INDIVIDUALLY AND KEPT MOVEMENT–CONSTRAINED THROUGH THE USE OF AN
12 ENCLOSURE OR TETHER MAY NOT:
13 (1) KEEP MORE THAN 5 ROOSTERS PER ACRE ON A SINGLE
14 PROPERTY; OR
15 (2) KEEP MORE THAN A TOTAL OF 25 ROOSTERS ON A SINGLE
16 PROPERTY.
17 (D) (1) THIS SECTION DOES NOT AFFECT THE AUTHORITY OF A COUNTY,
18 MUNICIPALITY, OR UNIT OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT TO ENACT AND ENFORCE
19 STANDARDS OR REQUIREMENTS RELATED TO ROOSTERS THAT ARE MORE
20 STRINGENT THAN THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS SECTION.
21 (2) THIS SECTION DOES NOT LIMIT OR SUPERSEDE ANY OTHER
22 COUNTY, MUNICIPAL, OR STATE LAW, RULE, OR REGULATION THAT PROVIDES MORE
23 STRINGENT REQUIREMENTS REGARDING THE KEEPING OF ROOSTERS.
24 (E) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES THIS SECTION IS:
25 (1) GUILTY OF A MISDEMEANOR AND ON CONVICTION IS SUBJECT TO
26 A FINE NOT EXCEEDING $1,000; OR
27 (2) SUBJECT TO ENFORCEMENT UNDER § 3–119 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
28 (F) THE DEPARTMENT MAY WORK IN COOPERATION WITH A LOCAL ANIMAL
29 CONTROL OR LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICER TO ENFORCE THIS SECTION.

4 SENATE BILL 375
1 (G) NOTHING IN THIS SECTION SHALL BE CONSTRUED TO REQUIRE THE
2 DEPARTMENT TO CONDUCT ADDITIONAL INSPECTIONS BEYOND THOSE
3 INSPECTIONS REQUIRED BY LAW.
4 (H) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS
5 SECTION.
6 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
7 October 1, 2025.

